num = app_dropped_na._get_numeric_data().columns.values

for col in num:
    if len(app_dropped_na[col].unique())<10 and col != 'TARGET':
        plt.subplots(figsize=(20,5))
        plt.title(col)
        plt.xticks(rotation='vertical')
        c = app_dropped_na.groupby(col).TARGET.sum()/app_dropped_na.groupby(col).TARGET.count()*100
        plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
        plt.xticks(rotation='vertical')
        #print(app_dropped_na.groupby(col).TARGET.count())
        sns.barplot(x = c.index, y = app_dropped_na.groupby(col).TARGET.count())
        plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
        plt.xticks(rotation='vertical')
        plt.ylabel("PROB_TARGET")
        sns.barplot(x = c.index, y = c.values)
